ems like an action advisory preparation task.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering native-image setup**\\n\\nI’m looking into the setup required for the native-image runtime based on system properties, which seems essential regardless of generated tests. The issue title points to native-image runs failing. I should make sure to use current_library version 5.0.0 and include sysprops in the build.gradle specifically for that version. It feels concrete that “new 5.0.1 requires the same system properties,” but I'm unsure about the determinism here. Should I run it locally with Java/native?\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Cla9SqKw3Tkba4031E0Axe4C|fc_031fcce86f5418e4016a41681593008197a7353692679a9ba4", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "cd tests/src/io.vertx/vertx-web-client/5.0.0 && GVM_TCK_LV=5.0.1 ../../../../../gradlew -q javaTest", "timeout": 120}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1050, "output": 1094, "cacheRead": 32256, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34400, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782671363834, "responseId": "resp_031fcce86f5418e4016a416804a3208197957642e16631121c"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_Cla9SqKw3Tkba4031E0Axe4C|fc_031fcce86f5418e4016a41681593008197a7353692679a9ba4", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "\nFAILURE: Build failed with an exception.\n\n* What went wrong:\nTask 'javaTest' not found in root project 'io.vertx.vertx-web-client_tests'.\n\n* Try:\n> Run gradlew tasks to get a list of available tasks.\n> For more on name expansion, please refer to https://docs.gradle.org/9.1.0/userguide/command_line_interface.html#sec:name_abbreviation in the Gradle documentation.\n> Run with --stacktrace option to get the stack trace.\n> Run with --info or --debug option to get more log output.\n> Run with --scan to generate a Buil